The Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries, or OPEC as it's more commonly known, is a rather significant entity in the grand, often grimy, theatre of global energy. Not to be confused with the more pedestrian [Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation](/Asia-Pacific_Economic_Cooperation), OPEC operates on a different scale, a different level of influence. It's an organization that, for better or worse, has shaped the world's relationship with oil for decades.

